	<div id="story">
		<h2>The Story</h2>

		<div class="row story_row very_well_padded">
			<div class="col-sm-3">
				<img src="assets/story_image_1.png">
			</div>
			<div class="col-sm-9">
				<p>
					<span class="p_starter">What is it? </span> A method developed from extensive academic research that combines <strong>tactile physical interaction</strong> with digital apps to help children learn a language, by replicating the way they naturally acquire language from birth.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row story_row very_well_padded">
			<div class="col-sm-3">
				<img src="assets/story_image_2.png">
			</div>
			<div class="col-sm-9">
				<p><span class="p_starter">How does it work? </span>We create interactive games and activities which children and parents play together. Children play learn their first sounds in a <strong>native accent</strong>, then words, then phrases. The first step is the Learning Cubes: read about them {{#link-to 'products'}}here.{{/link-to}}</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row story_row very_well_padded">
			<div class="col-sm-3">
				<img src="assets/story_image_3.png">
			</div>
			<div class="col-sm-9">
				<p><span class="p_starter">Why early years? </span>2 year olds are <strong>the world's best learners.</strong> Due to their brain plasticity, increased synaptic density, and other neurological factors, infants under the age of 6 absorb languages quickly and easily.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row story_row very_well_padded">
			<div class="col-sm-3">
				<img src="assets/story_image_4.png">
